fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
A twisting function \tau  is a family of maps \tau _n : B_n \to  G_{n-1} such that
  \begin {aligned}     \tau (\partial _k b) &= \partial _k \tau (b) && (k < n-1)\\     \tau (\partial _{n-1} b) &= \partial _{n-1} \tau (b) \cdot  \tau (\partial _n b) \\     \tau (\sigma _k b) &= \sigma _k \tau (b) && (k < n)\\     \tau (\sigma _n b) &= 1   \end {aligned}
  The corresponding simplicial map B_n \to  (\bar {W} G)_n is then computed by discarding the last k vertices of the input b \in  B_n for 1 \le  k \le  n, apply them to \tau  and placing them at the correct components.
